# seadog sudoers drop-in — install to /etc/sudoers.d/seadog, mode 0440.
#
# Lets the unprivileged `testenv` front-end shell out to the root helper
# `seadog-priv` (the elevation bridge in seadog::elevate). The wildcard
# matches ANY args on purpose: argument validation is the helper's job,
# NOT sudoers' — seadog-priv re-loads its own /etc/seadog/config.yaml and
# re-validates every argument independently (it trusts nothing from the
# front-end and does not even link the SSH-command parser). Trying to
# pin args in the sudoers match would be both brittle and a false sense
# of security. Verify with `visudo -cf` before install.
Defaults:testenv !requiretty, env_reset, secure_path="/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin"
testenv ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/lib/seadog/seadog-priv *
